705093f-a.text:
790-820 Jamaica Ave., south side, from Euclid Ave., to Crescent Street, showing in the background, a B.M.T. Elevated line.  The building in front of which is a truck, was once Harman's Casino Grove.  In 1873 it was Distler's Hotel and Brewery.

April 1923.

Eugene L Armbruster Collection.
